= SemanticSchemas test wiki =

This wiki was seeded by <code>php maintenance/importTestData.php</code>
with a Library/Books domain designed to exercise every feature of the
SemanticSchemas extension. Each entry below links to a page and calls
out the specific behavior it demonstrates, so you know what to look for.

== Content pages ==

=== Books ===

* '''[[The Hobbit]]''' — a single-inheritance [[:Category:Book]]
 instance. Look for: effective properties from [[:Category:Work]]
 (title, subtitle, pubyear) merged with Book's own (author, ISBN,
 genre, tag, availability). Three [[:Category:Chapter]] subobjects
 rendered in sort order. "Edit with form" tab should populate every
 field; chapters should appear in the multi-instance section of the
 form, not in free text.
* '''[[Dune]]''' — a [[:Category:ReviewedBook]] instance demonstrating
 '''multiple inheritance''' (Book + Reviewed). Look for: Book's full
 property table plus ''Review rating'' from [[:Category:Reviewed]].
 Three chapters ''and'' two reviews, each rendered with reviewer +
 rating + comment, both sections sorted.
* '''[[Introduction to Algorithms]]''' — a [[:Category:Textbook]]
 instance demonstrating a '''fully custom display template'''.
 [[:Category:Textbook]] sets <code>Has display format = none</code>
 and <code>Has display template = TextbookDisplay</code>, so rendering
 is delegated to [[Template:TextbookDisplay]]. Look for: green-bordered
 box with custom header + spotlight fields, followed by the full
 effective property table composed via <code>Category/display-rows</code>.

=== Articles ===

* '''[[Cosmos as Context]]''' — a [[:Category:Article]] sibling of
 [[:Category:Book]] under [[:Category:Work]]. Confirms ''Work''
 properties inherit into Article independently of Book. Also
 demonstrates the <code>URL</code>-typed property (<code>Has DOI</code>).

=== People ===

* '''[[J. R. R. Tolkien]]''' — a [[:Category:Person]] instance with the
 '''sidebox''' display format. Also demonstrates two more features:
 * '''Per-property row override''': [[Template:Category/property-row/Has email]]
   exists, so the email renders as a bold <code>mailto:</code> link rather
   than plain text — no other template touched.
 * '''Backlinks''': [[:Category:Person]] declares
   <code>show_backlinks_for = Has author</code> plus
   <code>[[:Property:Has author]]</code> has an
   <code>Inverse property label</code> of "Authored", so each Person sidebox
   ends with an "Authored ..." row listing works they wrote.
 Look at [[Frank Herbert]], [[Carl Sagan]], and [[Thomas Cormen]] for more
 Person instances.

== Schema shape ==

Category hierarchy (arrows point from child to parent):

 Work ← Book ← Textbook
 Work ← Book ← ReviewedBook → Reviewed
 Work ← Article
 Person (standalone; sidebox display)
 Chapter, Review (subobject-only types)

== Things worth clicking ==

* Any Person page → verify [[mailto:tolkien@example.org|mailto links]]
 render bold (per-property override).
* [[:Category:Work]] → inherited properties roll up through the hierarchy.
* [[Special:FormEdit/Book/The Hobbit]] → every field pre-populated;
 chapters in their own multi-instance section.
* [[Special:FormEdit/ReviewedBook/Dune]] → both chapters and reviews
 as separate multi-instance sections.
* [[Special:Ask]] with <code>[[Category:Book]]|?Has title|?Has genre</code>
 → returns Book, Textbook, and ReviewedBook instances via category
 inheritance (all three are children of [[:Category:Book]]).

== Customization reference ==

See [[mw:Extension:SemanticSchemas|Extension:SemanticSchemas]] docs
or <code>docs/user-guide/customizing-display.md</code> in the repo
for the four levels of display customization. Levels 2 (per-property
row) and 4 (fully custom display template) are live on this wiki.

